'''''Windsloe Mansion''''' is a [[text adventure]] published by [[SoftSide|Adventure of the Month Club]] for the [[Apple II]], [[Atari 8-bit computers]], and [[TRS-80]]. It was the January 1982 Adventure of the Month.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Adventure of the Month Ad |journal=SoftSide |date=January 1982 |issue=40 |page=[https://archive.org/details/softside-magazine-40/page/n14 13] |url=https://archive.org/details/softside-magazine-40}}</ref>

==Contents==
''Windsloe Mansion'' is a text adventure in which the player needs to rescue the Pumpkin Man from the haunted house where he is being held captive.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Bruce Campbell reviewed ''Windsloe Mansion'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 61.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Campbell |first=Bruce |date=March 1983 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=61|pages=41}}</ref> Campbell commented that "''Windsloe Mansion'' is a loser."<ref name="SG"/>

